Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.64,0:00:08.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief, \Nit's my turn next.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.01,0:00:10.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Saturday night, \Nunder the waning moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.67,0:00:14.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I shall seize the jewel upon the \Nhead of the untarnished nail,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.70,0:00:18.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and thus repay the debt I owe you\N from 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.42,0:00:28.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Long time no see,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.13,0:00:31.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.01,0:00:35.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike then, your partner here \Nisn't worth a damn.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.69,0:00:36.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Partner?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.76,0:00:43.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Female with 20 Faces" who dropped \Nout of sight in Paris 18 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.29,0:00:45.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.06,0:00:48.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.31,0:00:52.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! It's not deja vu!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.20,0:00:54.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the guy from 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.28,0:00:57.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mom told me this story the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.78,0:01:00.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It all started 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.69,0:01:03.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A Saturday night when the \Nfull moon was bright...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.43,0:01:10.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,See? What'd I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:11.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What's with the handcuffs?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.67,0:01:14.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And no sense having two of you, \Nso you'll disappear for good...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.72,0:01:21.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.92,0:01:28.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.40,0:01:30.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.44,0:01:35.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like what Mom was gushing \Nabout, how she and Dad first met!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.32,0:03:22.97,Signs - Thief Title,,0000,0100,15,,{\a3}{\fad(1000,0)}Phantom Lady and the Ryoma Treasure
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.28,0:03:22.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}So, what are you going to do,\N Kid the Phantom Thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.58,0:03:28.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can try to escape in \Nthat car like 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.78,0:03:33.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,except it was a\N slim motorcycle then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.81,0:03:38.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That car is compact, but not enough to fit \Nthrough the windows of this observation deck.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.24,0:03:46.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although, being a replica, \Nyou can't drive it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.91,0:03:47.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.05,0:03:53.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then this entire prized collection is a hoax.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.41,0:03:58.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And as for the big-ass ruby coming \Nin next week, it's actually a fake
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.08,0:04:02.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that you'll say was stolen by Kid,\N and then sell replicas on the black market.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.79,0:04:05.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all been arranged.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.39,0:04:08.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All I have to do now is take your life
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.01,0:04:10.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and send out our fake Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.77,0:04:13.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who do you think I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.69,0:04:19.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You really think you can take the life...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.40,0:04:20.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...of a phantom thief so easily?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.85,0:04:26.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't panic!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.96,0:04:28.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He has nowhere to escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.70,0:04:31.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as we block the elevator!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.56,0:04:34.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,K-Kid...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.04,0:04:35.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...vanished with the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.86,0:04:37.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.29,0:04:42.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That car makes engine noises,\N but it's a fake!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.61,0:04:44.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.03,0:04:47.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it should be a \Ndo-over of 18 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.68,0:04:50.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so I went ahead and arranged \Nthings like they were then...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.50,0:04:54.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're an idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.94,0:05:00.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He looped around behind us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.19,0:05:01.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.44,0:05:03.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let him get away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.99,0:05:08.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.41,0:05:12.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shiba Park is... over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.82,0:05:15.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe head-on won't work...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.17,0:05:20.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...but I can get through sideways!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.94,0:05:24.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Damn you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.38,0:05:28.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get out of here \Nbefore the cops come!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.43,0:05:30.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,P-President!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.43,0:05:31.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are those strange threads?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.66,0:05:43.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The height of Toto Tower's special \Nobservation deck is 250 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.19,0:05:46.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,250 = gt squared over 2...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:52.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Subtract air resistance and that gives us\N about 7.1 seconds 'til impact.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.35,0:05:55.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Enough time to spring \Nthis cheap handcuff...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.54,0:05:58.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One of their shots must've \Nripped a hole in my pocket!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.96,0:06:00.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My lock-picking wire is gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:03.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Crap! What do I do?! What do I do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.78,0:06:06.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wire! Wire! Wire!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.20,0:06:08.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.39,0:06:11.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Never forget your poker face, no matter what!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.25,0:06:14.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The hairpin!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.23,0:06:43.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, well, at least thanks to the commotion,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.79,0:06:45.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,those guys will probably \Nend up getting arrested.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.21,0:06:50.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They should be held as snug as bugs \Nfor a while with the thread I set up
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.22,0:06:52.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,while circling the car around.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.67,0:06:57.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, what do I do with this happy-go-lucky \Ngirl who slept through all the excitement?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.35,0:07:01.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My dad stole a kiss from my mom when \Nthey were in the same situation...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.09,0:07:07.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A-Although it's my fault \Nshe got mixed up in this...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:12.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'll let her have a rain check tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.21,0:07:18.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh, come on, Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.85,0:07:23.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You should've told me the bad guy from \N18 years ago was never sent to prison!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.00,0:07:25.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}The prosecutor's office is charging \NPresident Gouzu with suspicion of...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.66,0:07:27.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That guy put me through the wringer because \Nhe thought he was getting revenge!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:29.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But you caught him, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.68,0:07:31.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Great job...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.54,0:07:33.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kid the Phantom Thief II.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.28,0:07:39.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, Chikage-san, \Nwhen are you coming back to Japan?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.34,0:07:43.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My friend here has really taken a \Nliking to me and won't let me go back.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.90,0:07:46.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.14,0:07:50.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right. \NPresident Gouzu has apprentices,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.65,0:07:54.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and apparently, they're using the \Nsame methods to line their pockets.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.90,0:07:59.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A long time ago, I did my best \Nto gather up the evidence,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.34,0:08:04.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but I still never found the place where \Nthey stored all the fake merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.42,0:08:09.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So please teach them a lesson too, \NMagician Under the Moonlight.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.44,0:08:12.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I already mailed you a list of merchandise,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.02,0:08:14.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so I'm counting on you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.02,0:08:15.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,H-Hey! W-Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:23.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sakamoto Ryoma three-piece memento set?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.68,0:08:23.56,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,From: Kuroba Chikage\NSub: Ryoma Mementos\NSakamoto Ryoma three-piece memento set\NGun Belt\NHanging Scroll\NSake Cup
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.41,0:08:26.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a pain in the ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.80,0:08:33.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is it, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.13,0:08:38.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why are there so many?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.00,0:08:52.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think Chikage-sama has already told \Nyou what happened, Young Master,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.42,0:08:54.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but Phantom Lady,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.36,0:09:00.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,that is, Chikage-sama, didn't steal \Nall these items because she wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.48,0:09:08.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Gouzu sent out a fake notice using her name, \Nclaiming she would steal the Ryoma treasure.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.16,0:09:12.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. That's pretty much what Mom said.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.06,0:09:14.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They were using her, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.28,0:09:19.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They knew if they sent out a fake advance notice,\N Phantom Lady would definitely show up.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.42,0:09:24.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They tricked her into stealing the treasure, \Nthen mass-produced replicas themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.74,0:09:30.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and swindled collectors into buying the fakes \Nby claiming they were the stolen originals.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.62,0:09:35.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But Mom could tell the treasures she stole \Nwere fake and kept returning them to the cops.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.32,0:09:39.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, 18 years ago...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.20,0:09:42.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...they plotted to wipe out Chikage-sama.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.68,0:09:46.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Except, standing in their way was...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:50.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...my old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.88,0:09:54.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kuroba Toichi, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.05,0:09:58.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.01,0:10:04.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Toichi-sama saved Chikage-sama, then became \NKid the Phantom Thief to protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.06,0:10:12.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's nearly 20 years later, and their \Ndisciples are using the same means to get rich.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.67,0:10:18.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Mom asked me to \Ncapture them too, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.23,0:10:20.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.25,0:10:23.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,To that effect, Chikage-sama has gathered
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.93,0:10:29.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,all of these mass-produced replicas of \NRyoma's treasures from various collectors.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.13,0:10:32.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.22,0:10:34.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, they're all here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.59,0:10:38.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now the question is, how do I \Ncatch these guys in the act?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:41.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell me, Dad,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.87,0:10:43.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,what should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.86,0:11:04.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen, Kaito, and listen well.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.00,0:11:08.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When the magic's got you stumped, \Nyou can often find a hint
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.02,0:11:09.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,by thinking in reverse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.87,0:11:11.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking in reverse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.26,0:11:16.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Magicians always have to \Noutwit their audience.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.53,0:11:18.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If a certain idea is tripping you up,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.59,0:11:21.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you should think about an \Nexactly opposite method.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.87,0:11:26.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now {\i1}that{\i0} idea is sure to surprise them.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.28,0:11:28.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you understand, Kaito?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.86,0:11:39.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thinking in reverse...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.13,0:11:40.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.88,0:11:43.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.19,0:11:49.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is my one-time chance \Nto expose their misdeeds.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.01,0:11:50.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll show 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.63,0:11:57.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Kid the Phantom Thief \Ndoes more than just steal!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.78,0:12:15.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no need to be hasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.82,0:12:17.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I just have to wait for the right day.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.08,0:12:22.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's gonna return items that he stole?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.88,0:12:26.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is that what Kid's advance \Nnotice really said?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.91,0:12:27.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.87,0:12:33.25,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"One day soon, I'm going to show up at \Nthe currently-running Ryoma exhibition
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:35.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,to return three items.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.84,0:12:37.33,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.33,0:12:39.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-Three items?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.92,0:12:43.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Apparently, Tarumi Shishihiko-san, \Nthe sponsor of the Ryoma exhibition,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.96,0:12:47.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,did the same thing 20 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.01,0:12:50.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The three items were stolen then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.38,0:12:54.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The letter Sakamoto Ryoma's wife\N wrote him on a scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.66,0:12:58.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the night before he was assassinated,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.06,0:13:03.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,the soy sauce sake cup that became stained \Nwith his blood when he was assassinated,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.30,0:13:08.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and the concealed pistol that \NRyoma had on him at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.14,0:13:12.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was a Smith and Wesson type 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.10,0:13:15.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Look, that's what it says on \Nthe back of the advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.60,0:13:17.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.40,0:13:20.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,e-except Kid isn't the one \Nwho stole them, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.98,0:13:25.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, the "Female with 20 Faces." \NThe gentlewoman thief...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.18,0:13:28.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The Phantom Lady!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.49,0:13:33.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what the connection was \Nbetween Kid and Lady,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.20,0:13:36.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but after she stole those three items,\N Lady gave up a life of crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.93,0:13:40.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If you consider that Kid came on \Nthe scene two years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.84,0:13:44.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it may have been a master \Nand disciple relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.51,0:13:47.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So when is he coming?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.50,0:13:51.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know. It just says "one day soon" \Non the advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.44,0:13:56.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then let's cancel the Ryoma exhibition \Nimmediately and get the people out of there.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.78,0:14:01.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He withheld the date and time \Nto put us at a disadvantage!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.17,0:14:03.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Because he knows that it's easier \Njust to return something!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.57,0:14:07.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Nakamori-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.26,0:14:10.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He's offering to return stolen goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.40,0:14:12.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why should we reject that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.88,0:14:14.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know, but Superintendent...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.80,0:14:20.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, to catch Kid, we first \Nneed to invite him in, don't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.67,0:14:25.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Suzuki Jirokichi, the owner of the Suzuki \NMuseum, received the advance notice,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.28,0:14:27.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and he agrees with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.51,0:14:31.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,He said, "Leave the entrance \Nwide open and the exit narrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.11,0:14:35.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Those are the basics of \Ncatching a mouse."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.84,0:14:46.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I said I'd return 'em,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.14,0:14:50.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,but how can I bring in \Nall these faux treasures?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.02,0:14:58.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What the hell are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.83,0:15:00.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm on a diet!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.91,0:15:03.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My stomach's starting to get flabby,\N which is like a nightmare.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.87,0:15:07.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So I go like this and \Ntense my tummy muscles...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.30,0:15:12.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Jeez. I was wondering \Nwhat you were up to.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.52,0:15:15.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Too bad your tummy's starting to \Nstick out and not your chest, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.96,0:15:18.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.70,0:15:21.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't believe it! You always dodge it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.23,0:15:23.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks, Aoko.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.71,0:15:45.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing unusual at either \Nthe front or back entrances!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.73,0:15:46.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.86,0:15:47.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.74,0:15:52.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good job to you too, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.39,0:15:57.39,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ryoma Exhibition
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.00,0:16:23.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the gun belt Ryoma got\N from Takasugi Shinsaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:25.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Cool!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.52,0:16:27.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Although I'm sure it's a fake...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.81,0:16:31.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But nobody's looking at the treasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.63,0:16:33.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I guess that makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.77,0:16:35.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All of them are focused on...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:41.43,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Space reserved for Kid the Phantom Thief \Nto return treasures
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.94,0:16:49.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That Suzuki guy sure knows \Nhow to stir up a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.20,0:17:03.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.37,0:17:06.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Only that space has sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.18,0:17:10.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I-I'm sorry!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.02,0:17:12.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It was just meant to be a little prank...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.84,0:17:15.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And undercover cops are \Nmixed in with the crowd,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.55,0:17:21.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so they can quickly nab anyone \Nwho seems suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.29,0:17:28.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.81,0:17:30.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.65,0:17:41.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you all right, Conan-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.04,0:17:43.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.22,0:17:50.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We went to the trouble of coming here, but \Nit looks like Kid-sama may not even show up...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.22,0:17:52.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, why don't we go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.05,0:17:57.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it! I'm not leaving until \NI meet my beloved Kid-sama!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.85,0:18:06.85,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That twerp came here to be \Nthe fly in my ointment again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.85,0:18:14.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Their security is meticulous \Nthis time, Young Master.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.57,0:18:17.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And I bumped into a real troublemaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.24,0:18:22.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.08,0:18:25.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It seems this isn't going to be an easy job.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.12,0:18:28.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry. The wheels are \Nturning in my head, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.50,0:18:32.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master, do you have a plan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.62,0:18:35.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, wait and see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:38.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Jii-chan...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.92,0:18:41.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, Young Master?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.01,0:18:45.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's about time to hit \N'em with my next advance notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.83,0:18:47.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.67,0:18:49.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And what's it going to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.64,0:18:52.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got something in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.66,0:18:56.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A brilliant note befitting this job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.68,0:19:12.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Senior Adviser!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.42,0:19:15.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,S-Somebody just dropped this\N in the post box!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.63,0:19:19.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Th-This is one of \NKid's announcements?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.63,0:19:20.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:29.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Tomorrow at 8:00 pm,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.66,0:19:33.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,right before closing, I shall bring \Nover the pistol and other items,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.79,0:19:37.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and by the name of Sakamoto Ryoma, \Npatriot of the Bakumatsu period,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.82,0:19:42.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll give them a good washing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.42,0:19:44.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.42,0:19:46.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid the Phantom Thief is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.08,0:19:55.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But there's still something \Nfishy about all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.84,0:20:00.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid obviously didn't name the date \Nand time of his appearance this time,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.06,0:20:02.45,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,so why would he \Nsuddenly choose tomorrow?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.45,0:20:03.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Just maybe...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.68,0:20:08.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,...Kid was waiting for something until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.10,0:20:13.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.60,0:20:17.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.36,0:20:21.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.13,0:20:25.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid! Kid!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.18,0:20:26.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.69,0:20:56.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and rack your brains,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.22,0:20:59.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,you modern-day Sherlock Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.17,0:21:14.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master, as requested, \NI've prepared the props
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.78,0:21:17.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,for your next magic show.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.16,0:21:24.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.61,0:21:30.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Young Master, please be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.89,0:21:34.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, the police aren't \Nyour only adversaries.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.80,0:21:37.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I know!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.55,0:21:40.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet we're gonna have another \Nfun showdown this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.60,0:21:49.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't wanna miss this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.66,0:21:54.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The battle between me and my destined \Nrival, the pint-sized brilliant detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.43,0:21:57.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The illusion must go on!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.33,0:23:34.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I should've figured this job wouldn't be easy,\N since even Mom left it for me to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.60,0:23:39.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And it's made even worse with the involvement \Nof the brilliant munchkin detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.14,0:23:42.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,On the other hand, all of these \Nchallenges get me fired up!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.76,0:23:45.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, I'll pull off a magnificent \Nvictory with the aid of astounding magic!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:50.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on {\i1}Magic Kaito 1412{\i0}:\N Kid, Conan, and the Ryoma Treasure Illusion!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:50.15,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Kid, Conan, and the Ryoma Treasure Illusion
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.15,0:23:52.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Step right this way! Watch carefully!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.83,0:23:55.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's always one truth!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.00,0:23:56.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.32,0:23:58.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't miss the illusion!
